uploadType.name: uploadType
uploadType.description:
The type of upload request to the /upload URI. Acceptable values are

media - Simple upload. Upload the media only, without any metadata.

multipart - Multipart upload. Upload both the media and its metadata, in a single request.

callback.name: callback
callback.description: Callback function. Name of the JavaScript callback function that handles the response. Used in JavaScript JSON-P requests.

fields.name: fields
fields.description: Selector specifying a subset of fields to include in the response. For more information, see the partial response section in the Performance Tips document. Use for better performance.

prettyPrint.name: prettyPrint
prettyPrint.description: Returns response with indentations and line breaks. Returns the response in a human-readable format if 'true'. When this is 'false', it can reduce the response payload size, which might lead to better performance in some environments.

quotaUser.name: quotaUser
quotaUser.description:
Alternative to 'userIp'. Lets you enforce per-user quotas from a server-side application even in cases when the user's IP address is unknown. This can occur, for example, with applications that run cron jobs on App Engine on a user's behalf. You can choose any arbitrary string that uniquely identifies a user, but it is limited to 40 characters. Overrides 'userIp' if both are provided.
Learn more about capping usage.

userIp.name: userIp
userIp.description: IP address of the end user for whom the API call is being made. Lets you enforce per-user quotas when calling the API from a server-side application. Learn more about capping usage.

access_token.name: access_token
access_token.description:
Used to send a valid OAuth 2 access token. Do not use together with
the "Authorization" header

Authorization.name: Authorization
Authorization.description:
Used to send a valid OAuth 2 access token. Do not use together with
the "access_token" queryParameters string parameter.

methods.description: Media upload request. Directly inserts a message into only this user's mailbox. Does not send a message.
Media upload request. Sends the specified message to the recipients in the 'To', 'Cc', and 'Bcc' headers.
Media upload request. Directly imports a message into only this user's mailbox, similar to receiving via SMTP. Does not send a message.
